<Link id="l00135" /><CodeLine lineNumber="135"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Unlike LLVM values, Selection DAG nodes may return multiple</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00136" /><CodeLine lineNumber="136"><Highlight kind="comment">/// values as the result of a computation.  Many nodes return multiple values,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00137" /><CodeLine lineNumber="137"><Highlight kind="comment">/// from loads (which define a token and a return value) to ADDC (which returns</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00138" /><CodeLine lineNumber="138"><Highlight kind="comment">/// a result and a carry value), to calls (which may return an arbitrary number</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00139" /><CodeLine lineNumber="139"><Highlight kind="comment">/// of values).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00140" /><CodeLine lineNumber="140"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00141" /><CodeLine lineNumber="141"><Highlight kind="comment">/// As such, each use of a SelectionDAG computation must indicate the node that</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00142" /><CodeLine lineNumber="142"><Highlight kind="comment">/// computes it as well as which return value to use from that node.  This pair</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00278" /><CodeLine lineNumber="278"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Represents a use of a SDNode. This class holds an SDValue,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00279" /><CodeLine lineNumber="279"><Highlight kind="comment">/// which records the SDNode being used and the result number, a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00280" /><CodeLine lineNumber="280"><Highlight kind="comment">/// pointer to the SDNode using the value, and Next and Prev pointers,</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00282" /><CodeLine lineNumber="282"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00494" /><CodeLine lineNumber="494"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Represents one node in the SelectionDAG.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00495" /><CodeLine lineNumber="495"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00496" /><CodeLine lineNumber="496" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sdnode"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sdnode/#af64f53af99d4ee7bbf57ea0aab719254">SDNode</a> : </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">public</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a368e3de8ea854f34bc97c21a64d6a164">FoldingSetNode</a>, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">public</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/ilist-node">ilist&#95;node</a>&lt;SDNode&gt; &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00497" /><CodeLine lineNumber="497"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">private</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">:</Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00498" /><CodeLine lineNumber="498"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The operation that this node performs.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00499" /><CodeLine lineNumber="499"><Highlight kind="normal">  int32&#95;t NodeType;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00500" /><CodeLine lineNumber="500"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00501" /><CodeLine lineNumber="501"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/sdnodeflags">SDNodeFlags</a> Flags;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00502" /><CodeLine lineNumber="502"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00503" /><CodeLine lineNumber="503"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">protected</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00504" /><CodeLine lineNumber="504"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// We define a set of mini-helper classes to help us interpret the bits in our</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00505" /><CodeLine lineNumber="505"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// SubclassData.  These are designed to fit within a uint16&#95;t so they pack</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00506" /><CodeLine lineNumber="506"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// with SDNodeFlags.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00507" /><CodeLine lineNumber="507"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00508" /><CodeLine lineNumber="508"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#if defined(&#95;AIX) &amp;&amp; (!defined(&#95;&#95;GNUC&#95;&#95;) || defined(&#95;&#95;clang&#95;&#95;))</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00509" /><CodeLine lineNumber="509"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Except for GCC; by default, AIX compilers store bit-fields in 4-byte words</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00514" /><CodeLine lineNumber="514" lineLink="#a642fa8adfb997ef4036e740c30e8fb2a"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#define BEGIN&#95;TWO&#95;BYTE&#95;PACK()</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00515" /><CodeLine lineNumber="515" lineLink="#a27fbcacc15fbfe731744b87f733a9533"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#define END&#95;TWO&#95;BYTE&#95;PACK()</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00516" /><CodeLine lineNumber="516"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#endif</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01175" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1175"><Highlight kind="comment">/// When an SDNode is created from the DAGBuilder, the DebugLoc is extracted</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01176" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1176"><Highlight kind="comment">/// from the original Instruction, and IROrder is the ordinal position of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01177" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1177"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the instruction.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01178" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1178"><Highlight kind="comment">/// When an SDNode is created after the DAG is being built, both DebugLoc and</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l03053" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3053"><Highlight kind="comment">/// An SDNode that represents everything that will be needed</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03054" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3054"><Highlight kind="comment">/// to construct a MachineInstr. These nodes are created during the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03055" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3055"><Highlight kind="comment">/// instruction selection proper phase.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03056" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3056"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03057" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3057"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Note that the only supported way to set the &#96;memoperands&#96; is by calling the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03058" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3058"><Highlight kind="comment">/// &#96;SelectionDAG::setNodeMemRefs&#96; function as the memory management happens</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03059" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3059"><Highlight kind="comment">/// inside the DAG rather than in the node.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03060" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3060" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machinesdnode"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">MachineSDNode : </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">public</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sdnode/#af64f53af99d4ee7bbf57ea0aab719254">SDNode</a> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l03066" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3066"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03067" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3067"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// We use a pointer union between a single &#96;MachineMemOperand&#96; pointer and</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03068" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3068"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// a pointer to an array of &#96;MachineMemOperand&#96; pointers. This is null when</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03069" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3069"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// the number of these is zero, the single pointer variant used when the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03070" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3070"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// number is one, and the array is used for larger numbers.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03071" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3071"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03072" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3072"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// The array is allocated via the &#96;SelectionDAG&#96;&#39;s allocator and so will</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03073" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3073"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// always live until the DAG is cleaned up and doesn&#39;t require ownership here.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03074" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3074"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03075" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3075"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// We can&#39;t use something simpler like &#96;TinyPtrVector&#96; here because &#96;SDNode&#96;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03076" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3076"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// subclasses aren&#39;t managed in a conforming C++ manner. See the comments on</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03077" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3077"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// &#96;SelectionDAG::MorphNodeTo&#96; which details what all goes on, but the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03078" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3078"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// constraint here is that these don&#39;t manage memory with their constructor or</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03079" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3079"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// destructor and can be initialized to a good state even if they start off</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03080" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3080"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// uninitialized.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03081" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3081"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/pointerunion">PointerUnion&lt;MachineMemOperand &#42;, MachineMemOperand &#42;&#42;&gt;</a> MemRefs = &#123;&#125;;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l03083" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3083"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Note that this could be folded into the above &#96;MemRefs&#96; member if doing so</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03084" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3084"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// is advantageous at some point. We don&#39;t need to store this in most cases.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03085" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3085"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// However, at the moment this doesn&#39;t appear to make the allocation any</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03086" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3086"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// smaller and makes the code somewhat simpler to read.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03087" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3087"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">int</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> NumMemRefs = 0;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l03093" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3093"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Special case the common cases.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03094" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3094"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (NumMemRefs == 0)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03095" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3095"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &#123;&#125;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
